    "7 17On the other hand, only about 30% of Nobel Prize-winning works are published in Science, Nature, and PNAS, the three journals with the highest rejection rates.",
    "Correlation between these variables showed that high rejection rates correlated negatively with impact factor and with the number of articles published but correlated positively with work leading to a Nobel Prize.",
